.SH "NAME"
Perl::Critic::Policy::ControlStructures::ProhibitLabelsWithSpecialBlockNames \- Don't use labels that are the same as the special block names.
.SH "AFFILIATION"
.IX Header "AFFILIATION"
This Policy is part of the core Perl::Critic
distribution.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
When using one of the special Perl blocks \f(CW\*(C`BEGIN\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`END\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`CHECK\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`INIT\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`UNITCHECK\*(C'\fR, it is easy to mistakenly add a colon to the
end of the block name.  E.g.:
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    # a BEGIN block that gets executed at compile time.
\&    BEGIN { <...code...> }
\&
\&    # an ordinary labeled block that gets executed at run time.
\&    BEGIN: { <...code...> }
.Ve
.PP
The labels \*(L"\s-1BEGIN:\s0\*(R", \*(L"\s-1END:\s0\*(R", etc. are probably errors.  This policy
prohibits the special Perl block names from being used as labels.
.SH "CONFIGURATION"
.IX Header "CONFIGURATION"
This Policy is not configurable except for the standard options.
